<h2 id=3D"RobotFrameworkStyleGuideForOSI-RobotFramework">Robot Framework</h=
2>
<h2 id=3D"RobotFrameworkStyleGuideForOSI-FromtheRobotFrameworkMainPage:">Fr=
om the <a href=3D"https://robotframework.org/" class=3D"external-link" rel=
=3D"nofollow">Robot Framework</a> Main Page:</h2>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro has-no-icon confluence-informati=
on-macro-information">
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Robot Framework</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>is a generic open sou=
rce automation framework. It can be used for test automation and robotic pr=
ocess automation (RPA).</p>
<p>Robot Framework is actively supported, with many industry-leading compan=
ies using it in their software development.</p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(33,37,41);">Robot Framework is open and extens=
ible and can be integrated with virtually any other tool to create powerful=
 and flexible automation solutions. Being open source also means that Robot=
 Framework is free to use without licensing costs.</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Robot Framework has easy syntax, utilizing human-readable keywords. Its =
capabilities can be extended by libraries implemented with Python or Java. =
The framework has a rich ecosystem around it, consisting of<span>&nbsp;</sp=
an><a style=3D"text-decoration: none;" href=3D"https://robotframework.org/#=
libraries" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">libraries</a><span>&nbs=
p;</span>and<span>&nbsp;</span><a style=3D"text-decoration: none;" href=3D"=
https://robotframework.org/#tools" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"=
>tools</a><span>&nbsp;</span>that are developed as separate projects.</p>
<p>Robot Framework project is hosted on<span>&nbsp;</span><a style=3D"text-=
decoration: none;" href=3D"https://github.com/robotframework/robotframework=
" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">GitHub</a><span>&nbsp;</span>whe=
re you can find further documentation, source code, and issue tracker. Down=
loads are hosted at<span>&nbsp;</span><a style=3D"text-decoration: none;" h=
ref=3D"https://pypi.python.org/pypi/robotframework" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">PyPI</a>.</p>
<p>Robot Framework is operating system and application independent. The cor=
e framework is implemented using<span>&nbsp;</span><a style=3D"text-decorat=
ion: none;" href=3D"http://python.org/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofo=
llow">Python</a><span>&nbsp;</span>and also runs on<span>&nbsp;</span><a hr=
ef=3D"http://jython.org/" style=3D"text-decoration: none;" class=3D"externa=
l-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Jython</a><span>&nbsp;</span>(JVM) and<span>&nbsp;=
</span><a style=3D"text-decoration: none;" href=3D"http://ironpython.net/" =
class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">IronPython</a><span>&nbsp;</span>(=
.NET).</p>
<p>Robot Framework itself is open source software released under<span>&nbsp=
;</span><a style=3D"text-decoration: none;" href=3D"http://www.apache.org/l=
icenses/LICENSE-2.0.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Apache L=
icense 2.0</a>, and most of the libraries and tools in the ecosystem are al=
so open source. The framework was initially developed at<span>&nbsp;</span>=
<a href=3D"http://networks.nokia.com/" style=3D"text-decoration: none;" cla=
ss=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Nokia Networks</a><span>&nbsp;</span>=
and was open sourced in 2008.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p>Robot Framework can test just about anything, but in current context=
 it excels at Web UI, Mobile, REST API testing. It is capable of desktop ap=
plication, web socket, database, and ssh testing.</p>
