<h2 id=3D"RobotFrameworkStyleGuideForOSI-RobocopAndTheRules">Robocop And Th=
e Rules</h2>
<p>Robot Framework does have its community style that should be generally f=
ollowed and can be enforced by implementation of a Python package called <a=
 href=3D"/display/RFR/03+-+Robocop">Robocop</a>.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Robocop is the primary static code analysis tool for making sure Robot F=
ramework code is following standard community practices.</p>
<p>For setup and installation please refer to:&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/RFR=
/Cleaning+And+Organizing+Robot+Framework+Code">Cleaning And Organizing Robo=
t Framework Code</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/RFR/Visual+Studio+Co=
de+Setup">Visual Studio Code Setup</a></p>
<p>For reference to all the rules:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://robocop.readthed=
ocs.io/en/latest/rules.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https=
